communications.subject: Maryland Public Information Act Request: Maryland Parole Commission Permanent Denials
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Maryland Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Totals by aggregated offense categories for all individuals who were permanently denied parole by the Maryland Parole Commission during 2023 and 2024. No individual identifying information is required, only the total number of denials for each offense type.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jacob Wourms

title: Parole Commissioner and Hearing Examiner Employee Salaries

communications.subject: Maryland Public Information Act Request: Parole Commissioner and Hearing Examiner Employee Salaries
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Maryland Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

The most recent annual salaries for the following employees within the Maryland Parole Commission: 

Commissioners: Lisa A. Vronch, Robyn E. Lyles, John Dale Smack III, Denise Smith, Ernest Eley, Jr., Anthony J. McAllister, David Blumberg
Hearing Examiners: Mya Collins, Sharon Garrett, Chelsea Hicks, Sam Kelley, Charles Neverdon, Julie Nicholson, Kim Redditt, Ronald Williams, Tyler Wright, Gina Clay

Please provide each individual person's salary, not the total budget line item for commissioners and hearing examiners (sometimes referred to as "hearing officers").

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jacob Wourms

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: DPSS Digital Newsletters
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All DPSS Digital Newsletters from the inception of such newsletters through the most recent publication. According to the "DPSS Strategic Plan 2022-2027" (page 6) said newsletters were launched sometime during or after 2014.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Josh Seim
